# TOOLS.md
# Copy this file to TOOLS.md and fill in your values.
# TOOLS.md is gitignored — it contains local environment config.

## GitHub Task Board

Repo: `<GITHUB_ORG>/<ISSUES_REPO>`
Env override: `FORGE_GITHUB_TASK_REPO=<GITHUB_ORG>/<ISSUES_REPO>`

### Labels (workflow)
| Label | Meaning | Ray's action |
|-------|---------|--------------|
| `idea` | Not ready | Ignore |
| `ready` | Matt approved — pick up | Move to `in-progress`, act |
| `in-progress` | Being worked on | Monitor |
| `in-review` | PR open, waiting Matt | Notify Matt |
| `feedback` | Matt gave feedback | Pick back up, move to `in-progress` |
| `accepted` | Done | Matt sets this |

### Check the board (use this exact command — label filter is broken in older gh)
```bash
gh issue list --repo <GITHUB_ORG>/<ISSUES_REPO> \
  --json number,title,body,labels,updatedAt \
  | python3 -c "
import json, sys
issues = json.load(sys.stdin)
actionable = [i for i in issues if any(l['name'] in ['ready','feedback'] for l in i['labels'])]
stale = [i for i in issues if any(l['name'] == 'in-progress' for l in i['labels'])]
print('=== READY/FEEDBACK ===')
for i in actionable:
    labels = [l['name'] for l in i['labels']]
    print(f\"  #{i['number']} [{','.join(labels)}] {i['title']}\")
print('=== IN PROGRESS ===')
for i in stale:
    print(f\"  #{i['number']} {i['title']} (updated: {i['updatedAt'][:10]})\")
"
```

### Move a label
```bash
gh issue edit <n> --repo <GITHUB_ORG>/<ISSUES_REPO> \
  --remove-label <old> --add-label <new>
```

### Add a comment
```bash
gh issue comment <n> --repo <GITHUB_ORG>/<ISSUES_REPO> --body "<text>"
```

## Dev (Coding Agent)
Ray never writes code. Delegate to Dev by running Claude Code in the relevant workspace directory.

Handoff format:
```
Dev, implement [feature] on feat/[branch].

Repo: <GITHUB_ORG>/[repo]
Base: main → Your branch: feat/[branch]
GitHub Issue: #[n]
Model: claude-sonnet-4-6

1. Pull fresh from main
2. Create branch
3. Implement + tests
4. PR against main, link issue #[n], send URL
```

## Slack (Uplink)
Notification target: `<SLACK_CHANNEL_NAME>` (channel ID: `<SLACK_CHANNEL_ID>`)
Webhook URL: `<https://hooks.slack.com/services/...>`
Env override: `FORGE_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=<https://hooks.slack.com/services/...>`

For scheduled Forge runs, prefer the env var or a local `TOOLS.md` webhook entry so Python cron jobs can deliver alerts without an interactive MCP session.

---

# Tools Directory

External tools live in `tools/<name>/`. Each is a cloned repo. Re-clone via setup if missing.

## Attractor (Kinetic)

**Location:** `tools/attractor/`
**Repo:** `<GITHUB_ORG>/attractor`
**Role:** Kinetic — DOT-based pipeline execution engine

**Setup (if missing):**
```bash
cd tools && git clone git@github.com:<GITHUB_ORG>/attractor.git && cd attractor && npm install
```

**Usage:**
```
tools/attractor/attractor <pipeline.dot> [options]

Options:
  --dir <path>            Target project directory (default: cwd)
  --workspaces-dir <path> Attractor workspaces dir (default: .attractor/workspaces)
  --context key=value     Seed pipeline context (repeat for multiple)
  --sandbox               macOS only — DO NOT USE on Linux (see note below)
```

**Example:**
```bash
tools/attractor/attractor workspaces/my-project/pipelines/coding-task.dot \
  --dir workspaces/my-project \
  --context task_id=42 \
  --context task_title="Fix login bug"
```

**Linux sandbox note:**
`--sandbox` uses macOS `sandbox-exec` — omit it on Linux. Currently runs as `LocalExecutionEnvironment` (no sandboxing). Linux sandboxing via `firejail` is a future Kinetic task.

**Help:**
```bash
tools/attractor/attractor
```
